# reshapr-ui-control

This workspace hosts a lightweight UI used to inspect a local Reshapr control plane and MCP endpoints.

## Current scope

- PostgreSQL UI: `scripts/control-plane-ui.mjs` — default `http://localhost:555` (data via Docker `reshapr-postgres`)
- CLI-only UI: `scripts/control-plane-cli-ui.mjs` — default `http://localhost:1556` (`reshapr` CLI; second screen for comparison)
- Control plane base URL (display): `http://localhost:5555`
- Example MCP endpoint: `http://localhost:7777/mcp/reshapr/BlazeMeter+API/4`

## Functional goal

The UI should help operators:

- list Reshapr configurations
- list Reshapr expositions
- list available MCP tools from a selected endpoint (`initialize` + `tools/list`)

## Safety and behavior

- Keep this tool read-focused by default (inspection and diagnostics first).
- Avoid embedding secrets/tokens in code or docs.
- Use environment variables for configurable URLs and credentials.
